The paper deals with graph clustering algorithms, which is a topic in computer science that falls under several sub-categories. The focus on random-walk-based LOCAL algorithms suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The use of spectral algorithms and Laplacian eigenvalues suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the analysis of clustering accuracy and conductance suggests that it could belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
